modules.description: This module offers set operations like membership checks, unions, intersections, and differences, along with iteration, for generic elements, and provides collection manipulations such as searching, transformation, and partitioning for integer-based structures. It handles abstract types representing sets and list-like collections, enabling tasks like data filtering, mathematical set computations, and structured data processing. Specific use cases include optimizing query operations in databases or analyzing numerical datasets through efficient element traversal and modification.

This module offers set-theoretic operations such as membership checks, unions, intersections, and deletions, along with iteration capabilities, working with generic elements and structured collections. It also includes integer-focused functionalities like mapping, partitioning, min/max finding, and list conversions, enabling efficient manipulation of numerical data. These features are suited for tasks like mathematical set management and data transformation pipelines.

Provides operations for creating, merging, and querying sets of integers using Patricia trees. Works with integer sets and supports efficient membership checks, insertions, and unions. Used to manage large collections of unique integers with optimized memory and lookup performance.

Provides set operations like membership, union, intersection, and difference, along with iteration and transformation for integer-based structures. It supports abstract types for sets and list-like collections, enabling efficient data filtering, mathematical computations, and numerical analysis. Operations include mapping, partitioning, min/max retrieval, and list conversions. Examples include optimizing database queries and processing numerical datasets through structured element manipulation.
